HEADWORD: Subvaginal
<hw>Sub*vag"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated under or inside a sheath or vaginal membrane; <as>as, the
<ex>subvaginal</ex>, or subdural, spaces about the optic
nerve</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

